pull.title: [qa] Get rid of duplicate code
pull.body: This removes some unused and duplicate code in maxuploadtarget.py

events.body: Perhaps you could also do a similar replacement for pruning.py, which uses this same duplicated mine_full_block() function?
A couple of nits, otherwise ACK

rename.from: [qa] maxuploadtarget: Get rid of duplicate code

events.body:
@MarcoFalke @sdaftuar @mrbandrews Did you test this?
It seems to have slowed pruning.py by 35%.  I don't think its worth it at the expense of adding 10 mins to the pruning.py test.

Jup, I was running the tests after squash. Will take a look at the
slowdown. Should be easy to fix if this commit caused it.
@marcofalke my guess is it's the repeated calling of listunspent instead of caching the utxo's.  well I should say that's the first difference I saw and then was too tired to investigate further.

issue.title: [qa] Use cached utxo set to fix performance regression
issue.body:
I removed the caching in #9221, which made pruning take longer.

Credit goes to @morcos for quickly raising the issue: https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/9221#issuecomment-264683374
